<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="273" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1785,1954]" pageId="1" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1785,1810]" pageId="1" pageNumber="273">Remarks.</emphasis>
In addition to the species included below, some species currently classified in 
<taxonomicName box="[1231,1379,1785,1810]" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Dicranolaius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1231,1379,1785,1810]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="273">Dicranolaius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will certainly be transferred to 
<taxonomicName box="[448,528,1821,1846]" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Intybia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[448,528,1821,1846]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="273">Intybia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
after detailed examinations of the 
<typeStatus box="[920,968,1822,1846]" pageId="1" pageNumber="273">type</typeStatus>
specimens and additional material. 
<taxonomicName authority="Lea" authorityName="Lea" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Laius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="filamentarius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="273">Laius filamentarius</emphasis>
Lea
</taxonomicName>
was thought to be a true 
<taxonomicName box="[657,719,1858,1881]" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Laius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[657,719,1858,1881]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="273">Laius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wittmer" box="[767,944,1857,1882]" pageId="1" pageNumber="273" refString="Wittmer, W. (1952) Remarks on some Australian Laius Guer. (Col: Malachiidae). Proceedings of The Linnaean Society of New South Wales, 76,187 - 189." type="proceedings paper" year="1952">
Wittmer (
<number box="[878,936,1857,1882]" pageId="1" pageNumber="273" value="1952.0">1952</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
however, according to the current generic concepts (Evers 
<number box="[341,398,1894,1918]" pageId="1" pageNumber="273" value="1994.0">1994</number>
) this species should be classified in 
<taxonomicName box="[826,906,1893,1918]" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Intybia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[826,906,1893,1918]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="273">Intybia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the modified basal antennomeres in male, but with fore femur, tibia and tarsi simple without secondary sexual characters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
